        "Tourism management has added another layer of complexity to conservation efforts. The annual synchronised firefly event in the Smoky Mountains now requires a lottery system to limit visitor numbers, and the park service employs red-filtered torchlight and strict quiet protocols during peak displays. Even well-intentioned observers, if numerous enough, can suppress the very phenomenon they have come to witness.",
